{
  "answer": "**The third couplet (sher) of Allama Iqbal's poem in *Bang-e-Dara Part 1*, Chapter 2, reads as follows in English translation:**\n\n> O Lord, may my hope's garden thrive and gain,  \n> I fed these shoots with my own heart's blood-rain.[^1]\n\nThis matches the original Urdu (via transliteration):  \n*Phala phoola rahe ya Rab! Chaman meri umeedon ka*  \n*Jigar ka khoon de de kar yeh boote maine paale hain*[^2]\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/02-anokhi-waza-hai-saare-zamane-se-nirale-hain/translation/#p-61af92).\n[^2]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, Chapter 2 (transliteration). The couplets align sequentially across variants.[^3]\n\n[^3]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, [Chapter 2 (translation)](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/02-anokhi-waza-hai-saare-zamane-se-nirale-hain/translation/).",
